```
 ok so lets analyze...

On the migration process, TableMigration.  Im trying to relate a Table to an other Table->uuid.

ht issue is on this line: 
```swift
 .column("roomId", .uuid, .notNull, .references("chats\".\"Room", onDelete: .cascade, onUpdate: .noAction))
```
While declaring the `references` I get that the **Table Room** dose not exist even though it was created successfully, the error resigns that the Table is with in a Schema (directory). So I fix it with ** "chats\".\"Room" ** since this will force the query builder to create the correct reference 

The next issue is also regarding Table Schema

```swift
// -> **batchInsert**

    private var batchInsertQuery: SwifQLable {
        var data: [String: [SwifQLable]] = [:]
        self.forEach { table in
            table.columns.forEach {
                let value: SwifQLable = ($0.property.inputValue as? SwifQLable) ?? SwifQL.default
                if var d = data[$0.name.label] {
                    d.append(value)
                    data[$0.name.label] = d
                } else {
                    data[$0.name.label] = [value]
                }
            }
        }
        let columns = data.keys.sorted(by: { $0 > $1 })
        var values: [[SwifQLable]] = []
        enumerated().forEach { i, _ in
            columns.enumerated().forEach { n, c in
                if let v = data[c]?[i] {
                    if values.count < i + 1 {
                        values.append([v])
                    } else {
                        values[i].append(v)
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return SwifQL
            .insertInto(**Element.tableName**, fields: columns.map { Path.Column($0) })
            .values
            .values(array: values)
    }
```
I created a function imitating this function changing:
```
**Element.tableName** to **Element.table**
```
